# id: IndexedSorter -> void sort(IndexedSortable s, int l, int r)_
commentText: Sort the items accessed through the given IndexedSortable over the given_range of logical indices. From the perspective of the sort algorithm,_each index between l (inclusive) and r (exclusive) is an addressable_entry.__@see IndexedSortable#compare_@see IndexedSortable#swap
